    "Since offloading is a pervasive and transformative feature of human cognition, we have reason to think that it is constitutively dependent on the resources offloading incorporates.",
    "In (§4) I showed how this rosy picture for HEC comes into conflict with action theory's standard story -I outlined a narrative of how this account came to be widely adopted, taking Davidson's influential arguments as paradigmatic.",
    "At this point, we have two options: retract the radical claims of (§3) or abandon the standard story.",
    "In (§5) I set out one way of taking the second route, sketching and motivating a view inspired by Anscombe's alternative picture.",
    "Having mapped a patch of logical space, I did some work to make the Anscombean corner of it look hospitable to naturalists."
